    <div class="body">
      One potential positive of gas price spikes and then Russia's decision to go to war is that people are more acutely aware that relying on unstable regimes for supplies of key resources isn't such a great idea, and reducing volatility and increasing energy security is a good plan.<br /><br />Even if Europe is heading to greener energy, doing it faster becomes key to reduce dependence on Russia, and replacing coal with gas is less of a stop gap solution when your gas supplies are expensive and from Russia.<br /><br />It turns it from a climate issue to a national security one which might get everyone on the same page and supporting action, even if it's for the &quot;wrong&quot; reasons.
      
