    <div class="body">
      I’m optimistic that the supply side will be very responsive to the cost of solar/wind falling dramatically.  If there’s more profit to be made there than burning fossil fuels, industry will head that direction.  I would like to see a carbon tax to help that along, but I’d settle for cap &amp; trade.<br /><br />Where I think we need massive .gov investment is on the demand side.  Many people simply can not or will not rip &amp; replace working cars, furnaces, etc.  We should be subsiding the hell out of them on a sliding scale all the way to ‘free EV’ for the truly poor.
      
