      <div class="quotetitle"><a href="https://arstechnica.com/civis/viewtopic.php?p=40807331#p40807331" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">sigmasirrus</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So what’s the worst case scenario? What would be the effects?</div><br /><br />That was the subject of the second part of the 6th Assessment Report. Have a look at the <a href="https://arstechnica.com/science/2022/03/if-adapting-to-climate-change-sounds-easy-it-shouldnt/" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">impacts of climate change</a> link in the article.<br /><br />But just for a few highlights:<br />- Around 10% of all fish species going extinct<br />- Humanitarian crises, especially as small island nations go under water<br />- Increasing weather extremes, which we're already seeing around the world<br />- 50-75% of the world's population exposed to periods of life-threatening extreme heat and humidity by the end of the century (i.e. within my child's lifetime)<br />- Lower food security and nutrition<br /><br />(And most of that is at 2 degrees of warming, far from the worst case scenario)
      
